(1, '<b>Bengaluru</b>', 'City in Karnataka', '<h4>\" Garden city of India \"</h4>Bengaluru (also called Bangalore) is the capital of India\'s southern Karnataka state. The center of India\'s high-tech industry, the city is also known for its parks and nightlife. By Cubbon Park, Vidhana Soudha is a Neo-Dravidian legislative building. Former royal residences include 19th-century Bangalore Palace, modeled after Englandâ€™s Windsor Castle, and Tipu Sultanâ€™s Summer Palace, an 18th-century teak structure. <br> Having evolved gradually from being the Garden city to the Silicon Valley of India, Bangalore is India\'s third-largest city. Bangalore is loved for its pleasant weather, beautiful parks and the many lakes here. Bangalore is renowned for its eateries, street food corners, quirky cafes, coffee roasters and pubs dotting every corner of the city, serving cuisines from all over the world. Brunches, buffets, burgers, rooftop cafes, late-night eats - Bangalore has it all.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d248849.88653998985!2d77.4908528388935!3d12.953959987220104!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3bae1670c9b44e6d%3A0xf8dfc3e8517e4fe0!2sBengaluru%2C%20Karnataka!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1632139506892!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"280\" height=\"200\" style=\"border:0; float: right; margin: 0 0 15px 0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', 'Karnataka, India', '<div id=\"c9a0c8920e2bf841eb376dee955d8e5f\" class=\"ww-informers-box-854753\" style=\" float:right; margin-right:155px;\"><p class=\"ww-informers-box-854754\"><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/india/bangalor/7days/\">Bangalore - weather forecast</a><br><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/saint_paul/\">world-weather.info</a></p></div><script async type=\"text/javascript\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://world-weather.info/wwinformer.php?userid=c9a0c8920e2bf841eb376dee955d8e5f\"></script><style>.ww-informers-box-854754{-webkit-animation-name:ww-informers54;animation-name:ww-informers54;-webkit-animation-duration:1.5s;animation-duration:1.5s;white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;-o-text-overflow:ellipsis;text-overflow:ellipsis;font-size:12px;font-family:\'Lora\', serif;line-height:18px;text-align:center}@-webkit-keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}@keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}</style>', '<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Bengaluru/b_slide_1.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Bengaluru/b_slide_2.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Bengaluru/b_slide_3.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Bengaluru/b_slide_4.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">'),
(2, '<b>Mumbai</b>', 'City in Maharashtra', '<h4>\" The City of Dreams \"</h4>Mumbai (formerly called Bombay) is a densely populated city on India\'s west coast. A financial center, it\'s India\'s largest city. On the Mumbai Harbour waterfront stands the iconic Gateway of India stone arch, built by the British Raj in 1924. Offshore, nearby Elephanta Island holds ancient cave temples dedicated to the Hindu god Shiva. The city\'s also famous as the heart of the Bollywood film industry. <br> Mumbai, the capital city of the Indian state of Maharashtra, is a spectacular paradox of chaos and hope, glamour and squalor, modernity and tradition. Famously known as the City of Dreams, Mumbai formerly known as Bombay - Mumbai is a beautifully blended melting pot of cultures and lifestyles. One of the main centres in the country of art, culture, music, dance and theatre, Mumbai is a dynamic, cosmopolitan city that has been running for years solely on the indomitable spirit of the Mumbaikars.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d241317.11609836016!2d72.74109984136237!3d19.08219783949479!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3be7c6306644edc1%3A0x5da4ed8f8d648c69!2sMumbai%2C%20Maharashtra!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1632227153739!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"280\" height=\"200\" style=\"border:0; float: right; margin: 0 0 15px 0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', 'Maharashtra, India', '<div id=\"de9eec7b5591ecf7da43a945c9c2cb21\" class=\"ww-informers-box-854753\" style=\" float:right; margin-right:155px;\"><p class=\"ww-informers-box-854754\"><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/india/mumbai/7days/\">Weather in Mumbai for 7 days</a><br><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/washington_1/\">https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/washington_1/</a></p></div><script async type=\"text/javascript\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://world-weather.info/wwinformer.php?userid=de9eec7b5591ecf7da43a945c9c2cb21\"></script><style>.ww-informers-box-854754{-webkit-animation-name:ww-informers54;animation-name:ww-informers54;-webkit-animation-duration:1.5s;animation-duration:1.5s;white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;-o-text-overflow:ellipsis;text-overflow:ellipsis;font-size:12px;font-family:\'Lora\', serif;line-height:18px;text-align:center}@-webkit-keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}@keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}</style>', '<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Mumbai/m_slide_1.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Mumbai/m_slide_2.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Mumbai/m_slide_3.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Mumbai/m_slide_4.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">'),
(3, '<b>Kashmir</b>', 'City in Jammu & Kashmir', '<h4>\" Paradise on Earth \"</h4>Kashmir is world famous for its scenic splendour, snow-capped mountains, plentiful wildlife, exquisite monuments, hospitable people and local handicrafts. Your trip to Jammu and Kashmir will be a memorable one as the state will not only appeal to you with its scenic beauty and snow-covered mountain ranges, but the adventure sports will take you to a different world. Nestled in the Himalayan, Pir Panjal and Karakoram mountain ranges are renowned for their natural beauty and gentle people. <br> Jammu and Kashmir is dotted with the most beautiful mountain peaks, massive glaciers, splendid monasteries, blue lakes, rivers, forests, verdant meadows and tall pine trees. While sports like Skiing, golf, trekking, river rafting, paragliding, camping make the trip to Jammu and Kashmir more adventurous, Amarnath and Vaishno Devi attract a large number of pilgrims every year. Dal Lake, Kashmir Valley, Khardung La Pass, Gulmarg, Shalimar Bagh are some of the major attractions of the state. The unparalleled beauty and charm of the state and the sweetness of the residents will remain etched in your memory forever.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1697647.2049551625!2d74.17880742719237!3d33.7938004608582!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x38fd5a18725ced0f%3A0x631f6613ace0ce12!2sJammu%20%26%20Kashmir!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1632240545804!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"280\" height=\"200\" style=\"border:0;  float: right; margin: 0 0 15px 0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', 'Jammu & Kashmir, India', '<div id=\"f0efac19a858cdf791d68d67026e40e3\" class=\"ww-informers-box-854753\" style=\" float:right; margin-right:165px;\"><p class=\"ww-informers-box-854754\"><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/india/jammu/\">Weather in Kashmir</a><br><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/boston/\">https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/boston/</a></p></div><script async type=\"text/javascript\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://world-weather.info/wwinformer.php?userid=f0efac19a858cdf791d68d67026e40e3\"></script><style>.ww-informers-box-854754{-webkit-animation-name:ww-informers54;animation-name:ww-informers54;-webkit-animation-duration:1.5s;animation-duration:1.5s;white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;-o-text-overflow:ellipsis;text-overflow:ellipsis;font-size:12px;font-family:\'Lora\', serif;line-height:18px;text-align:center}@-webkit-keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}@keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}</style>', '<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Kashmir/k_slide_1.jpg\" style=\"margin: 5px; width:600px; height:525px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Kashmir/k_slide_2.jpg\" style=\"margin: 5px; width:600px; height:525px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Kashmir/k_slide_3.jpg\" style=\"margin: 5px; width:600px; height:525px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Kashmir/k_slide_4.jpg\" style=\"margin: 5px; width:600px; height:525px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Kashmir/k_slide_5.jpg\" style=\"margin: 5px; width:600px; height:525px; border-radius: 12px;\">'),
(4, '<b>Hyderabad</b>', 'City in Telangana', '<h4>\" The City of Nizams \"</h4>A city of contrasts, Hyderabad exudes an old-world charm of its own with the Old City (Charminar side), Hitech City (Cyberabad) and the other areas lying between the old and the new. The capital and the largest city of Telanaga, Hyderabad is home to stately mosques and noisy bazaars lined parallelly alongside swanky new office buildings and malls, and it is these very contrasts â€“ these glimpses into the cityâ€™s rich past with inherent promises of an even better future â€“that make Hyderabad a city worth visiting. Maybe even more than once. <br> The city of pearls and biryani, Hyderabad is home to one of the most iconic landmarks - The Charminar, a 16th-century mosque whose 4 arches support towering minarets, each of them facing a different street, is an old city landmark near the long-standing Laad Bazaar. The Charminar stands in a labyrinth of lanes crammed with shops, markets, stalls and shoppers - one of the best places to shop for the authentic pearls and relish the tasty biryanis, skewer kebabs and haleem (the smorgasbord of food that Hyderabad is known for).Its historic sites include Golconda Fort, a former diamond-trading center that was once the Qutb Shahi dynastic capital.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d487295.02532044525!2d78.12785129924684!3d17.41215307568293!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3bcb99daeaebd2c7%3A0xae93b78392bafbc2!2sHyderabad%2C%20Telangana!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1632242343365!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"280\" height=\"200\" style=\"border:0; float: right; margin: 0 0 15px 0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', 'Telangana, India', '<div id=\"af093d9ca0aaa28fdb29371e5e530872\" class=\"ww-informers-box-854753\" style=\" float:right; margin-right:165px;\"><p class=\"ww-informers-box-854754\"><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/india/hyderabad/\">Weather in Hyderabad</a><br><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/raleigh/\">Weather Forecast in Raleigh</a></p></div><script async type=\"text/javascript\" charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://world-weather.info/wwinformer.php?userid=af093d9ca0aaa28fdb29371e5e530872\"></script><style>.ww-informers-box-854754{-webkit-animation-name:ww-informers54;animation-name:ww-informers54;-webkit-animation-duration:1.5s;animation-duration:1.5s;white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;-o-text-overflow:ellipsis;text-overflow:ellipsis;font-size:12px;font-family:\'Lora\', serif;line-height:18px;text-align:center}@-webkit-keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}@keyframes ww-informers54{0%,80%{opacity:0}100%{opacity:1}}</style>', '<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Hyderabad/h_slide_1.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Hyderabad/h_slide_2.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Hyderabad/h_slide_3.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">\r\n<img class=\"mySlides\" src=\"Media/Hyderabad/h_slide_4.jpg\" style=\"margin: 10px; width:575px; height:400px; border-radius: 12px;\">'),
(5, '<b>Kolkata</b>', 'City in West Bengal', '<h4>\" The city of Joy \"</h4>Kolkata, India\'s second biggest city, is a perpetually ongoing festival of human existence, concurrently luxurious and squalid, refined and frantic, pointedly futuristic, while beautifully in decay. A vibrant 350-year-old metropolis located on India\'s Eastern Coast, the capital of West Bengal thrives on contradictions and imposing spectacles; nothing is commonplace in this city. Kolkata is, in every sense, the artistic, cultural and intellectual capital of the country. <br> Kolkata\'s streets are vivid, hectic, chaotic, and yet, brimming with life and creativity. Driven by the indomitable spirit of the self-made middle class, the city has created a beautiful juxtaposition of the old colonial-era charm with the nascent upcoming hipster culture that thrives amongst the city\'s millennial residents. Kolkata\'s street food is famous all across the country, and the city is lined with eateries and food stalls at every corner, where you can savour local Bengali food, or try out local snacks such as Jhalmuri, or Ghugni Chaat.', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d471238.2709303211!2d88.04998924003215!3d22.670598250581424!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39f882db4908f667%3A0x43e330e68f6c2cbc!2sKolkata%2C%20West%20Bengal!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1632399689842!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"280\" height=\"200\" style=\"border:0; float: right; margin: 0 0 15px 0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', 'West Bengal, India', '<div id=\"8e9aa3e1e73283d096ea68590d014aa5\" class=\"ww-informers-box-854753\" style=\" float:right; margin-right:165px;\"><p class=\"ww-informers-box-854754\"><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/india/kolkata/14days/\">Weather in Kolkata for 14 days</a><br><a href=\"https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/montgomery_1/\">https://world-weather.info/forecast/usa/montgomery_1/</a></p></div><script async type=\"text/javasc